Durban - Police Minister Bheki Cele said three people have been arrested in connection with incendiary devices which were placed in and around Durban including retail stores.  
At a press briefing in Durban on Friday, Cele said a joint multidisciplinary intensive investigation led to the arrest. 

In July bombs were found at the Woolworths stores in Gateway and Pavilion. People had to be evacuated. The store has since begun searching its customers. 

 







