  Police Minister Bheki Cele at a press briefing in Durban on Friday. Video: Karinda Jugmohan
 


Cele said the "three targets" have been arrested for placing and detonating of these devices, as well other crimes. 

"Between March and August in Durban and surrounding areas were plagued with several incidents of placing and detonating of these devices," said Cele. 
"In a separate incident that was linked to the placing of these devices three men were attacked in May this year at the mosque in Verulam that left one person dead and 2 others critically injured," said Cele. 

